radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to a maximum of 1.2 cm with periappendiceal fat stranding and mildly thickened and hyperemic walls. Small perihepatic free fluid noted. No drainable fluid collection. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Normal liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, and urinary bladder.
